'''Jyoti Prakash Tamang''' (born 11 November 1961) is an Indian [[food technology|food technologist]], [[microbiologist]] and the officiating vice chancellor of the [[Sikkim University|Sikkim Central University]]. Known for his studies on [[fermented food]], Tamang is an elected fellow of the [[National Academy of Agricultural Sciences]], Indian Academy of Microbiological Sciences and the Biotech Research Society of India. The [[Department of Biotechnology]] of the Government of India awarded him the [[National Bioscience Award for Career Development]], one of the highest Indian science awards, for his contributions to biosciences in 2004.

== Biography ==
Jyoti Prakash Tamang was born on 16 November 1961 in the mountain district of [[Darjeeling]] in the Indian state of [[West Bengal]]  from [[Nepali Indian|Nepali parents]].<ref name="NABS fellow">{{Cite web |url=http://nabsindia.org/profiles/jyotiprakashtamang.html |title=NABS fellow |date=2017-12-12 |website=National Academy of Biological Sciences |access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref> He completed his schooling at Turnbull High School, Darjeeling in 1977 and his pre-university course at the [[St Joseph's College, Darjeeling]] in 1979.<ref name="NAAS Fellows">{{Cite web |url=http://naasindia.org/detail.php?id=556 |title=NAAS Fellows |date=2017-12-06 |website=National Academy of Agricultural Sciences |access-date=2017-12-06}}</ref> His undergraduate education was at the [[Darjeeling Government College]] of [[North Bengal University]] from where he passed BSc honors in 1982 and continued at the institution to earn an MSc in microbiology in 1984, passing the examination winning a gold medal for academic excellence.<ref name="Faculty profile">{{Cite web |url=http://www.cus.ac.in/index.php/en/schools/life-sciences/108-home/schools/life-sciences/department-of-microbiology/478-updated-prof-jyoti-prakash-tamang |title=Faculty profile |date=2017-12-12 |website=Sikkim University |language=en-gb |access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref> He started his career in 1986 as an associate professor at the department of botany of [[Sikkim Government College, Tadong]] where he worked until 2011. Simultaneously, he enrolled at North Bengal University for his doctoral studies and after securing a PhD in microbiology in 1992, he did his post-doctoral work at two institutions abroad during 1994–95; first at the National Food Research Institute, [[Tsukuba]] with a fellowship from the [[United Nations University]]-[[Kirin Brewery Company]] and, later, at the Institute of Hygiene and Toxicology, [[Karlsruhe]], on a fellowship received from [[Volkswagen Foundation]]. In 2011, he joined [[Sikkim University|Central Sikkim University]] (CUS) as a member of faculty and has been serving the institution since then. He has held various positions at the university which included those of an academic coordinator, the dean of the School of Life Sciences, the registrar (the first registrar of the university) and a professor (presently the senior-most professor at CUS). He also serves as the officiating vice chancellor of the university.<ref name="Jyoti Prakash Tamang on Sikkim University">{{Cite web |url=http://cus.ac.in/index.php/en/department-of-microbiology/prof-jyoti-prakash-tamang |title=Jyoti Prakash Tamang on Sikkim University |date=2017-12-12 |website=cus.ac.in |language=en-gb |access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref> In between, he had a short stint at the Research Institute of Humanity and Nature of the Ministry of Education, Science and Technology, [[Kyoto]] as a visiting professor during 2009–10.<ref name="NABS fellow" />

== Legacy ==
[[File:Beer and bread.jpg|thumb|235px|Beer and bread, two major uses of [[fermentation]] in food]]
Tamang focused his research on the culture, microbiology, nutrition, and functional property of food and is known to be an expert on [[fermented food]] in use across the world.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ourworld.unu.edu/en/contributors/jyoti-prakash-tamang |title=Jyoti Prakash Tamang - Our World |date=2017-12-12 |website=ourworld.unu.edu |access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref> He is reported to have identified the [[probiotic]] and functional properties of fermented food found in the Himalayan region and has studied its microbial diversity.<ref name="Jyoti Prakash Tamang on Sikkim University" /> His studies have been documented by way of a number of articles<ref name="Jyoti Prakash Tamang on Loop">{{Cite web |url=https://loop.frontiersin.org/people/24652/overview |title=Jyoti Prakash Tamang on Loop |date=2017-12-12 |publisher=Frontiers Media |access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref><ref name="On Google Scholar">{{Cite web |url=https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=TSawMGoAAAAJ&hl=en |title=On Google Scholar |date=2017-11-23 |publisher=Google Scholar |access-date=2017-11-23}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Please see ''Selected bibliography'' section}} and [[ResearchGate]], an online repository of scientific articles has listed 36 of them.<ref name="On ResearchGate">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Jyoti_Tamang |title=On ResearchGate |date=2017-11-23 |publisher=On ResearchGate |access-date=2017-11-23}}</ref> Besides, he has published four books namely, ''Himalayan Fermented Foods: Microbiology, Nutrition, and Ethnic Values'',<ref name="Himalayan fermented foods : microbiology, nutrition, and ethnic values">{{Cite book |url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/488384742 |title=Himalayan fermented foods : microbiology, nutrition, and ethnic values |last=Prakash. |first=Tamang, Jyoti |date=2010 |publisher=CRC Press |isbn=9781420093247 |location=Boca Raton |oclc=488384742}}</ref> ''Ethnic fermented foods and alcoholic beverages of Asia'',<ref name="Ethnic fermented foods and alcoholic beverages of Asia">{{Cite journal |title=Ethnic fermented foods and alcoholic beverages of Asia |url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/956376305 |location=India |isbn=9788132228004 |oclc=956376305}}</ref> ''Fermented foods and beverages of the world''<ref name="Fermented foods and beverages of the world">{{Cite book |url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/668418271 |title=Fermented foods and beverages of the world |date=2010 |publisher=CRC Press/Taylor & Francis |isbn=9781420094954 |location=Boca Raton |oclc=668418271}}</ref> and ''Health benefits of fermented foods and beverages''.<ref name="Health benefits of fermented foods and beverages">{{Cite book |url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/906025866 |title=Health benefits of fermented foods and beverages |last=Tamang |first=Jyoti Prakash |isbn=9781466588097 |location=Boca Raton |oclc=906025866}}</ref>

== Awards and honors ==
Tamang received the Women's Association Award of the [[United Nations University]] in 1996.<ref name="NABS fellow" /> The [[Department of Biotechnology]] of the Government of India awarded him the [[National Bioscience Award for Career Development]], one of the highest Indian science awards in 2004.<ref name="Awardees of National Bioscience Awards for Career Development">{{Cite web |url=http://dbtindia.nic.in/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/list_of_bioscience_awardees.pdf |title=Awardees of National Bioscience Awards for Career Development |date=2016 |publisher=Department of Biotechnology |access-date=2017-11-20}}</ref> He was elected as a fellow by the Biotech Research Society of India in 2006 and he received the Gourmand World Cookbook Award in 2010; the same year as he received the elected fellowship of the Indian Academy of Microbiological Sciences.<ref name="NABS fellow" /> The elected fellowship of the [[National Academy of Agricultural Sciences]] reached him in 2016.<ref name="NAAS Fellows" />

